<subSubSection id="14B8651DCA41FFE7D7F1FDADFEBFFC14" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5C1D3696CA41FFE7D7F1FDADFEBFFC14" blockId="4.[151,1437,610,961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D7F1FDADFE8EFDF4" bold="true" box="[151,267,610,636]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from only one specimen collected in Northern 
<collectingCountry id="24B57606CA41FFE7D325FDADFB0EFDF4" box="[1091,1163,610,636]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.Although in the original description, the unique specimen, the 
<typeStatus id="83198834CA41FFE7D52EFD49FD28FD28" box="[584,685,646,672]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">holotype</typeStatus>
, was said to be in the NMNH, it was not found in this collection. Based on the features provided in the original description, this species agrees with the definition of the 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA41FFE7D265FD65FA19FD4C" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[1283,1436,682,708]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
A. 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D242FD65FA19FD4C" box="[1316,1436,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group as I proposed here. The male has a short costal bulla on each forewing, segment VII bears a double ventral process, segment IX bears paired dorsolateral processes, and the inferior appendages are relatively short and not fused mesally. 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA41FFE7D65AFCD9FDA3FCB8" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[316,550,790,816]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elvesta">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D65AFCD9FDA3FCB8" box="[316,550,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Acostatrichia elvesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA41FFE7D53CFCD8FD3CFCB8" authority="Santos, 2020" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pes" authorityYear="2020" box="[602,697,791,817]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D53CFCD8FDEEFCB9" box="[602,619,791,817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D51EFCD8FD3CFCB8" box="[632,697,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">araca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D5D9FCD9FC92FCB8" bold="true" box="[703,791,790,816]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="75E557FFCA41FFE7D5D9FCD9FC92FCB8" box="[703,791,790,816]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share the condition of having two ocelli, whereas all other 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA41FFE7D7F1FCF5FEABFCDC" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[151,302,826,852]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D7F1FCF5FEABFCDC" box="[151,302,826,852]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Acostatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have three. The male genitalia of these two species are quite different, especially with segment IX apparently bearing two pairs of dorsolateral processes in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA41FFE7D41BFC90FC6FFCF0" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[893,1002,862,889]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elvesta">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D41BFC90FC0BFCF1" box="[893,910,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA41FFE7D4FAFC91FC6FFCF0" box="[924,1002,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">elvesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the subgenital plate being divided longitudinally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
